## Part One

```elixir
hash = fn char_list ->
  char_list
  |> Enum.reduce(0, fn curr, acc ->
    acc
    |> Kernel.+(curr)
    |> Kernel.*(17)
    |> rem(256)
  end)
end

hash.(String.to_charlist("HASH")) == 52
```

```elixir
part_one = fn input ->
  input
  |> parse.()
  |> Enum.map(&hash.(&1))
  |> Enum.sum()
end

part_one.(test_input) == 1320 &&
  part_one.(input)
